The Property of the Huygens Family of Brussels, Sale Sotheby Parke Bernet, London, July 7, 1976, N° 9 repr. in sale catalogue; [toegevoegde vermelding]: 'F.G. Panel, 14 x 19 in (36 x 48,5 cm). Inscribed, [onderstreept] later in black, bottom right, near centre: 'P. BRUEGHEL'. column4: <content>1 zw/w foto, verso: P. Bruegel II, The Peasant and the Bird Nester, Panel, 36 x 48,5 cm (14 x 18""). The Property of the Huygens Family of Brussels, Sale Sotheby Parke Bernet, London, July 7, 1976, N° 9 repr. in sale catalogue; [toegevoegde vermelding]: 'F.G. Panel, 14 x 19 in (36 x 48,5 cm). Inscribed, [onderstreept] later in black, bottom right, near centre: 'P. BRUEGHEL'. Extended on the right beyond the Vienna painting, comparable to the Uffizi drawing, which allows the conclusio that the Vienna painting was cut down on the right. Not in Marlier. The lotus flower in the bottom right corner, left out! Bought by Mr. Charles de Pauw, (Wavres-Brussels for £ 22000).'</content>
